in_\u0110ER=9|draw_\u0110ER=1|loss_\u0110ER=20|gf_\u0110ER=34|ga_\u0110ER=51|status_\u0110ER=R\n|win_HAJ=6|draw_HAJ=4|loss_HAJ=20|gf_HAJ=32|ga_HAJ=76|status_HAJ=R\n\n|col_P=green1|text_P=Promotion to [[2015\u201316 Serbian First League|Serbian First League]]\n|result1=P\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to [[Serbian Zone League|Zone League]]\n|result14=R|result15=R|result16=R\n\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.srbijasport.net/tak/1769/rez/ Srbijasport] at srbijasport.net\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150924015756/http://www.fsris.org.rs/Aktuelnosti/aktuelnosti.html Aktuelnosti FSRIS] at fsris.org.rs\n\n{{Serbian League East}}\n{{2014\u201315 in Serbian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2014-15 Serbian League East}}\n[[Category:Serbian League East seasons]]\n[[Category:2014\u201315 in Serbian football leagues|3]]\n[[Category:2014\u201315 in European third tier association football leagues|Serb]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition      = Serbian League East\n| season           = 2014-2015\n| winners          = [[FK Dinamo Vranje|Dinamo Vranje]]\n| promoted         = [[FK Dinamo Vranje|Dinamo Vranje]]\n| relegated        = Kopaonik; \u0110erdap; Hajduk Veljko\n| matches          = 490\n| total goals      = 717\n| league topscorer = \n| biggest home win = {{ubl\n|[[FK Radni\u010dki Pirot|Radni\u010dki Pirot]] 8:1 Hajduk Veljko;\n|[[FK Sin\u0111eli\u0107 Ni\u0161|Sin\u0111eli\u0107 Ni\u0161]] 7:0 Sloga Despotovac;\n|[[FK Radni\u010dki Pirot|Radni\u010dki Pirot]] 7:0 Sloga Despotovac\n}}\n| biggest away win = Sloga 2:7 [[FK Radni\u010dki Pirot|Radni\u010dki Pirot]]\n| highest scoring  = Radni\u010dki Svilajnac 6:4 Kopaonik\n| prevseason       = [[2013\u201314 Serbian League East|2013\u201314]]\n| nextseason       = [[2015\u201316 Serbian League East|2015\u201316]]\n}}\nThe '''2014\u201315''' [[Serbian League East]] season. It began on 16 August 2014 and ended on 7 June 2015. [[Serbian League East]] is one of four Serbian league in football, which is the third level of football contest in Serbia . League consists of 16 teams . A higher level of competition is the [[First League of Serbia|First League]] , while the lower three [[Serbian Zone League|Zone League]] - West , East and South.\n\n==Clubs 2014\u201315==\n\n===Teams and Stadiums===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Team\n!City\n!Stadium\n!Capacity\n|-\n|{{sort|Car Konstantin|[[FK Car Konstantin|Car Konstantin]]}}\n|{{sort|Ni\u0161|[[Ni\u0161]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Car Konstantin|Stadion FK Car Konstantin}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Dinamo|[[FK Dinamo Vranje|Dinamo]]}}\n|{{sort|Vranje|[[Vranje]]}}\n|{{sort|Vranje Stadium|Stadion [[Yumco]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5,000\n|-\n|{{sort|\u0110erdap|\u0110erdap}}\n|{{sort|Kladovo|[[Kladovo]]}}\n|{{sort|Kladovo Stadium|Gradski stadion Kladovo}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3,000\n|-\n|{{sort|[[Hajduk Veljko]]|Hajduk Veljko}}\n|{{sort|Negotin|[[Negotin]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Negotin|Gradski Stadion Negotin}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Kopaonik|Kopaonik}}\n|{{sort|Brus|[[Brus]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Brus|Stadion FK Kopaonik }}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2,000\n|-\n|{{sort|OFK Bor|[[FK Bor|OFK Bor]]}}\n|{{sort|Bor|[[Bor, Serbia|Bor]]}}\n|{{sort|Bor stadium|Stadion kraj Pirita}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Ozren|[[FK Ozren Sokobanja|Ozren]]}}\n|{{sort|Soko Banja|[[Sokobanja]]}}\n|{{sort|Soko banja stadium|Stadion Bata Nole}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Radan|Radan}}\n|{{sort|Lebane|[[Lebane]]}}\n|{{sort|Lebane stadium|Gradski stadion Lebane}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Radnicki Pirot|[[FK Radni\u010dki Pirot|Radni\u010dki Pirot]]}}\n|{{sort|Pirot|[[Pirot]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Pirot|[[Stadion kraj Ni\u0161ave]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|13,816\n|-\n|{{sort|Radnicki Svilajnac|[[FK Radni\u010dki Svilajnac|Radni\u010dki Svilajnac]]}}\n|{{sort|Svilajnac|[[Svilajnac]]}}\n|{{sort|Bojaca|Stadion Boja\u010da}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1,000\n|-\n\n|{{sort|Sindjelic|[[FK Sin\u0111eli\u0107 Ni\u0161|Sin\u0111eli\u0107]]}}\n|{{sort|Ni\u0161|[[Ni\u0161]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion FK Masinac|Stadion FK Sin\u0111eli\u0107}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Sloga|Sloga Despotovac}}\n|{{sort|Despotovac|[[Despotovac]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Despotovac|Stadion FK Sloga}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Tabane 1970|Tabane 1970}}\n|{{sort|Jagodina|[[Jagodina]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Tabane|Stadion FK Tabane}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Timok|[[FK Timok|Timok]]}}\n|{{sort|Zajecar|[[Zaje\u010dar]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Kraljevica|Stadion Kraljevica}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|10,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Timocanin|[[FK Timo\u010danin|Timo\u010danin]]}}\n|{{sort|Knjazevac|[[Knja\u017eevac]]}}\n|{{sort|Stadion Knjazevac|Gradski stadion Knja\u017eevac}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4,000\n|-\n|{{sort|Trstenik|Trstenik PPT}}\n|{{sort|Trstenik|[[Trstenik, Serbia|Trstenik]]}}\n|{{sort|Gradski Stadion Trstenik|Gradski Stadion Trstenik}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3,000\n|-\n|}\n\n==League table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=PR\n\n|team1=DIN|name_DIN=[[FK Dinamo Vranje|Dinamo V.]]\n|win_DIN=21|draw_DIN=2|loss_DIN=7|gf_DIN=57|ga_DIN=30\n|team2=RPI|name_RPI=[[FK Radni\u010dki Pirot|Radni\u010dki P.]]\n|team3=TRS|name_TRS=Trstenik PPT\n|team4=CAR|name_CAR=[[FK Car Konstantin|Car Konstantin]]\n|team5=TIM|name_TIM=[[FK Timok|Timok]]\n|team6=RAD|name_RAD=Radan\n|team7=TAB|name_TAB=Tabane 1970\n|team8=RSV|name_RSV=[[FK Radni\u010dki Svilajnac|Radni\u010dki S.]]\n|team9=BOR|name_BOR=[[FK Bor|OFK Bor]]\n|team10=OZR|name_OZR=[[FK Ozren Sokobanja|Ozren]]\n|team11=TMC|name_TMC=[[FK Timo\u010danin|Timo\u010danin]]\n|team12=SLO|name_SLO=Sloga D.\n|team13=SIN|name_SIN=[[FK Sin\u0111eli\u0107 Ni\u0161|Sin\u0111eli\u0107 N.]]\n|team